history.content: The general waitlist position does not matter as much. The important thing is as are you waiting on an open lab. If you have space to get off the waitlist for your lab you will be good. If your lab is full you will be skipped.

children.subject: I got off the waitlist today and I was number 265 or something. If you can't get in the lab then you won't get in the class

So, the lab that I tried to enroll in has an enrollment of 27 out of 38 people. In addition, for that lab section, 21 people are waitlisted. Since the sum of the currently enrolled and the number waitlisted is greater than the number of seats, should I look for a new lab? There are some lab sections in which the sum of the number enrolled and the number waitlisted is less than the total number of seats.

Say I was on position 62 on the waitlist, and I dropped out cuz my lab had a full waitlist of 26 seats. Then, I readded and now my lab has 3 open seats and no one on the waitlist. Is this safe? Will I probably get in?
